Note:- Encapsulation - Hide data and expose it through methods.

Many developers think Encapsulation = private variables.
That's not completely correct.

Encapsulation actually has three parts:

1. Bundle data and methods into one class.
2. Hide the internal data.
3. Control access through methods or properties.

============================================================
OOPS CONCEPT #1 - ENCAPSULATION
============================================================

Definition

Encapsulation is the process of combining data (variables) and
behavior (methods) into a single unit (class), while restricting
direct access to the data.

In simple words,

"Hide the data and allow access only through controlled methods."

============================================================
1. WHAT IS ENCAPSULATION?
============================================================

Encapsulation means:

✔ Keep variables inside a class.
✔ Control how those variables are accessed.
✔ Prevent unauthorized modification.

Everything is packed inside one class.

Example

Customer Class

-----------------------------------
Customer
-----------------------------------
Variables
- Name
- Email
- Phone

Methods
- getName()
- setName()
- getEmail()
- setEmail()

Everything belongs to one class.

============================================================
Real-Life Analogy
============================================================

Think about an ATM.

What you can do

✔ Withdraw Money
✔ Deposit Money
✔ Check Balance

What you CANNOT do

✘ Open the ATM machine
✘ Change your account balance manually
✘ Modify bank database

You interact only through buttons.

The internal implementation is hidden.

This is Encapsulation.

============================================================
2. WHY IS ENCAPSULATION USED?
============================================================

It is used to

• Protect data
• Prevent invalid data
• Improve security
• Make code easier to maintain
• Hide implementation details
• Control how data is modified

Without encapsulation, Anyone can modify your variables.
With encapsulation, Only approved methods can modify data.

============================================================
