============================================================
4. HOW IS IT USED?
============================================================

Using

• private variables
• public methods
• getters
• setters

Syntax

public class Employee{

    private Decimal salary;

    public void setSalary(Decimal amount){

    }

    public Decimal getSalary(){

    }

}

============================================================
Example 1
============================================================

Without Encapsulation

public class Employee{

    public Decimal salary;

}

Now anyone can write

Employee e = new Employee();

e.salary = -10000;

Wrong data is stored.

============================================================
Example 2
============================================================

Using Encapsulation

public class Employee{

    private Decimal salary;

    public void setSalary(Decimal amount){

        if(amount > 0){

            salary = amount;

        }

    }

    public Decimal getSalary(){

        return salary;

    }

}

Usage

Employee emp = new Employee();

emp.setSalary(50000);

System.debug(emp.getSalary());

Output

50000

Now

emp.setSalary(-2000);

Nothing happens because validation fails.

