============================================================
5. ADVANTAGES
============================================================

1. Protects data.
2. Prevents invalid values.
3. Improves security.
4. Easier maintenance.
5. Reduces bugs.
6. Centralizes validation.
7. Makes code reusable.
8. Hides implementation details.

============================================================
6. DISADVANTAGES / LIMITATIONS
============================================================

1. Slightly more code.
2. Need getter/setter methods.
3. Can become verbose if overused.
4. Poorly designed methods can still expose data incorrectly.

============================================================
7. ALTERNATIVE APPROACHES
============================================================

Instead of exposing variables

Use

• Properties (getter/setter)

Example

public String name {get; set;}

Instead of

public String name;

Properties are cleaner and commonly used in Apex.

============================================================
8. BEST PRACTICES
============================================================

✔ Keep variables private whenever possible.
✔ Expose data through methods or properties.
✔ Validate data before updating variables.
✔ Never expose sensitive data directly.
✔ Keep business rules inside the class.
✔ Don't make every variable public.

============================================================
9. COMMON MISTAKES
============================================================

Mistake 1

Making every variable public.
Wrong :- public Decimal salary;
Correct :- private Decimal salary;

------------------------------------

Mistake 2

No validation.

salary = -1000;

Always validate.

------------------------------------

Mistake 3

Changing variables directly from another class.
Always use methods.

